[debug] [2026-02-19T01:03:08.602Z] <<< [apiv2][status] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/thefaypateffect-920b3/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask 200
[debug] [2026-02-19T01:03:08.602Z] <<< [apiv2][body] POST https://cloudaicompanion.googleapis.com/v1beta/projects/thefaypateffect-920b3/locations/global/instances/default:completeTask {"output":{"messages":[{"content":"Let's craft some GraphQL operations for your app using Firebase Data Connect! I'll create four distinct operations—two queries and two mutations—with proper authentication directives based on your provided schema.\n\nHere's what I've come up with:\n\n```graphql\nquery AllNewsArticles @auth(level: PUBLIC, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to the public as it retrieves general news articles.\") {\n  newsArticles(orderBy: [{publishedAt: DESC}], limit: 10) {\n    id\n    title\n    imageUrl\n    publishedAt\n    author {\n      name\n      role\n    }\n  }\n}\n\nquery EventsByLocation($location: String!) @auth(level: PUBLIC, insecureReason: \"This operation is safe to expose to the public as it retrieves events based on a specified location.\") {\n  events(where: {location: {eq: $location}}, orderBy: [{date: ASC}]) {\n    id\n    name\n    date\n    time\n    location\n    description\n    registrationLink\n  }\n}\n\nmutation CreateInitiative($title: String!, $description: String!, $startDate: Date, $endDate: Date, $imageUrl: String) @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This operation allows any logged-in user to create an initiative, which is a design choice for this application.\") {\n  initiative_insert(data: {\n    title: $title\n    description: $description\n    startDate: $startDate\n    endDate: $endDate\n    imageUrl: $imageUrl\n  }) {\n    id\n  }\n}\n\nmutation UpdateTeamMemberBio($id: UUID!, $newBio: String!) @auth(level: USER, insecureReason: \"This operation allows any logged-in user to update a team member's bio, which is a design choice for this application.\") {\n  teamMember_update(key: {id: $id}, data: {\n    bio: $newBio\n  }) {\n    id\n  }\n}\n```\n\nLet's break down these operations:\n\n1.  **`AllNewsArticles` (Query):** This query fetches the 10 most recent news articles, including their ID, title, image URL, publication date, and the author's name and role. It's marked as `PUBLIC` because displaying general news is typically safe for all users, logged in or not.\n\n2.  **`EventsByLocation` (Query):** This query allows you to retrieve events happening in a specific location, ordered by date. I've marked this as `PUBLIC` because event listings are generally publicly accessible.\n\n3.  **`CreateInitiative` (Mutation):** This mutation allows a user to create a new initiative by providing a title, description, and optional start date, end date, and image URL. I've set this to `USER` level authentication, assuming that any logged-in user has permission to create initiatives in your application.\n\n4.  **`UpdateTeamMemberBio` (Mutation):** This mutation enables updating the `bio` of a `TeamMember` given their `id`. This is also set to `USER` level, as we're assuming any logged-in user has the privilege to update team member bios in this app scenario.\n\nHere are a few follow-up questions you might consider:\n\n*   Could you provide an example of a query that uses a more complex `where` clause, perhaps combining multiple conditions with `_and` or `_or`?\n*   How would I write a mutation to delete an existing `Event`?\n*   Can you show me an example of how to use a server-side expression (like `auth.uid`) within a query's `where` clause for filtering?","author":"model"}]},"outputDataContext":{"additionalContext":{"@type":"type.googleapis.com/google.cloud.cloudaicompanion.v1main.ChatOutputDataContext","relatedContent":{}}},"attributionContext":{"citationMetadata":{}}}
